(
  'Why Coaches Need a Quiz Instead of a PDF Lead Magnet',
  'quiz-vs-pdf-lead-magnet',
  '2026-04-11',
  'The PDF lead magnet had its moment. That moment has passed. Here''s why coaches who switch to a quiz get warmer leads, better insight into their audience, and a funnel that runs itself.',
  E'Most coaches have a PDF gathering dust on their website.\n\nYou know the one. "10 Steps to [Transformation]." Designed at midnight. Downloaded by nobody. Or downloaded by everyone and read by no one.\n\nThe PDF lead magnet had its moment. That moment has passed.\n\nHere''s why quizzes work better — and why coaches specifically are sitting on a goldmine they haven''t touched yet.\n\n## The problem with a PDF\n\nA PDF is a one-way street.\n\nYou put information out. Your visitor takes it. You get an email address if you''re lucky. You get zero insight into who that person actually is, what they''re struggling with, or whether they''re the right fit for your programme.\n\nSo you end up with a list full of people you know nothing about. You send the same email to all of them. You wonder why your open rates are falling.\n\nThe PDF doesn''t qualify anyone. It just collects.\n\n## What a quiz does differently\n\nA quiz asks questions before it gives anything away.\n\nThat matters for two reasons.\n\nThe first is psychological. When someone answers questions about themselves, they''re invested. They want to know what their answers mean. Completion rates for quizzes are dramatically higher than for PDFs because curiosity is a more powerful motivator than free information.\n\nThe second reason is practical. By the time a prospect sees their results, you already know something about them. What they''re struggling with. Where they are in their journey. Which of your offers is the right fit.\n\nYou haven''t spoken to them yet. But you already know them.\n\nThat''s the difference between a cold lead and a warm one.\n\n## The two-way win coaches miss\n\nHere''s what most coaches don''t realise when they first look at quizzes.\n\nYes, your prospect gets value. They get a personalised result that feels tailored to them. They feel seen. That''s good.\n\nBut you get something too. You get structured data on every single person who takes your quiz. Which result type is most common in your audience. What problems your ideal clients are naming for themselves. Where the gaps are in your market.\n\nThat''s market research happening automatically, every time someone clicks your quiz link.\n\nMost coaches spend money on surveys and discovery calls trying to understand their audience. A quiz does it quietly, in the background, for free.\n\n## Why this matters especially for coaches\n\nCoaches sell transformation. That''s inherently personal.\n\nA generic form that asks for a name and email tells your prospect nothing about how well you understand them. A quiz that asks the right questions and returns a result that sounds like you''ve read their mind — that builds trust before you''ve said a word.\n\nThink about the last time you took a personality quiz or a business assessment and the result nailed exactly where you are. You probably shared it. You probably wanted to know more about whoever made it.\n\nThat''s what a well-built coaching quiz does. It positions you as someone who gets it before the discovery call even happens.\n\n## The objection I hear most\n\n"I don''t have time to build something complicated."\n\nThat was a fair objection two years ago. It isn''t now.\n\nPretaQuiz was built specifically for coaches who want a branded lead-generation quiz on their website without a developer, without a monthly agency retainer, and without spending a week figuring out the tech.\n\nYou pick a template built for your niche. You add your branding, your questions, your results. You get a link. You share it.\n\nThat''s it. Most coaches have their quiz live in under an hour.\n\nOne payment. No monthly fee. No tech skills required, ever.\n\n## What to do with your PDF\n\nDon''t bin it.\n\nTurn it into your results content. If your quiz has four result types, write one result description that points to the relevant section of your PDF. Now your PDF is doing a job — it''s the thing warm leads receive after they''ve already told you who they are.\n\nThat''s a