(
  'What to Put on Your Coaching Website to Get More Discovery Calls',
  'coaching-website-discovery-calls',
  '2026-04-11',
  'Your coaching website should be doing the qualification work before a prospect ever reaches out. Here''s what to add — and what to cut — to turn more visitors into booked calls.',
  E'Most coaching websites have the same problem.\n\nThey explain what the coach does. They list the benefits. They have a "Book a call" button somewhere near the bottom.\n\nAnd then they wonder why the calendar stays quiet.\n\nThe issue is not your copy. It''s not your colours. It''s not even your offer.\n\nIt''s that your website is asking visitors to take a big leap of faith with very little in return.\n\nHere''s how to change that.\n\n## What your visitor is actually thinking\n\nWhen someone lands on your website for the first time, they''re not thinking about booking a call. They''re thinking about whether you understand their problem.\n\nThey''re scanning for signals. Does this coach get what I''m going through? Have they worked with people like me? Do they know what it feels like to be where I am right now?\n\nIf the answer feels like yes, they move forward. If it feels like maybe, they leave.\n\nYour website has about ten seconds to answer that question before they''re gone.\n\n## What most coaches put on their website\n\nMost coaching websites lead with credentials. The coach''s story. Their methodology. Their framework.\n\nAll of that is relevant. None of it is what your visitor needs to see first.\n\nYour visitor needs to see themselves. Their problem. Their situation. Before they care about you, they need to feel understood.\n\nThe fastest way to create that feeling is not better copy. It''s interaction.\n\n## The thing that changes everything\n\nA quiz changes the dynamic of your website completely.\n\nInstead of your visitor passively reading about you, they''re actively telling you about themselves. They''re answering questions. They''re engaged. They''re curious about their result.\n\nAnd the result — if it''s written well — gives them the "this person gets it" moment that no homepage copy can reliably create.\n\nThat moment is what converts a visitor into a lead. And a lead into a booked call.\n\n## What a good coaching quiz looks like\n\nIt''s short. Five to seven questions. Each one feels relevant, not generic.\n\nIt covers where they are right now, what they''ve tried, and what''s getting in the way. Not surface-level stuff. The questions your best clients would recognise immediately.\n\nThe results are written in their language. Not coaching jargon. The exact words your clients use when they describe their own situation.\n\nAnd at the end, there''s a clear next step. Usually a button to book a discovery call. With a line that connects their result to why that conversation makes sense.\n\nThat''s the flow. Visitor lands. Visitor takes quiz. Visitor sees result. Visitor books call.\n\nNo chasing. No following up with people who downloaded a PDF and went cold. Just warm, qualified people who already feel a connection with you arriving in your calendar.\n\n## What to cut from your website\n\nWhile you''re at it.\n\nCut the long bio on the homepage. Move it to an About page.\n\nCut the generic "I help coaches achieve their potential" headline. Replace it with the specific problem you solve for the specific person you help.\n\nCut the contact form as your primary CTA. Replace it with your quiz.\n\nA contact form asks for commitment. A quiz offers value first. That difference matters more than any other change you can make to your site.\n\n## How to get your quiz live today\n\nPretaQuiz gives you a branded lead-generation quiz built for your coaching niche. Pick your template, add your branding and questions, and get a link you can drop on your homepage today.\n\nNo developer. No monthly subscription. No three-hour setup.\n\nOne payment. Live in under an hour.\n\nYour discovery call calendar should be working harder than it is. A quiz is the fastest way to make that happen.\n\n[Get your quiz live today at pretaquiz.com](https://pretaquiz.com)'
